<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref">
	Author, Initial(s) Year of publication, <em>Title of book</em>, Publisher, Place of publication.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Examples</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref">
	<span class="hover" title="Author">Andreasen</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Initial(s)">NC</span>
	<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2001</span>,
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of book">Brave new brain: conquering mental illness in the era of the genome</span></em>,
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Oxford University Press</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Place of publication">Oxford</span>.
</blockquote>
<br>
For a numbered edition, place the abbreviation after the book title. This part should not be italicised. 
Use rev. edn, for revised editions.
<br>
<blockquote class="ref">
	<span class="hover" title="Author">Andreasen</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Initial(s)">NC</span>
	<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2001</span>,
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of book">Brave new brain: conquering mental illness in the era of the genome</span></em>,
	<span class="hover" title="Edition">2nd edn</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Oxford University Press</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Place of publication">Oxford</span>.
</blockquote>
